rComments: Very nice but quite boring. To be fair, the subject matter is not of the most interesting, but I feel like even the most boring subjects can be made interesting by the right prof. Unfortunately, that is not the case with Mr. Boase.

Professor Boase is one of the most soft spoken and approachable Profs I have had at UTM. While going to lectures about Methodologies are not necessarily interesting, he is always reachable for extra help and is glad to explain concepts.  If you do your readings and listen to the lectures its very easy to get an A in both tests and assignments.

Grading on the first paper was a little rough given the outline was not detail specific. Tests rely heavily on lecture content but lectures are boring and difficult to sit through, in class and online. Two weekly lectures, one in class and one online, both are mandatory.
